<p align="center"><span style="font-size: 24pt;"><b>Instructions for
Reviewers<br>
</b></span></p>
<ol>
  <li>This review form is intended to be used for electronic submission
of reviews. When handling this electronic form, please adhere to this:</li>
</ol>
<ul>
  <dir>
  <dir>
  <ul>
    <li>Use ASCII code only. </li>
    <li>Do not use tabs. </li>
    <li>Confirm that the review is yours if the Associate Editor asks
for confirmation. </li>
  </ul>
  </dir>
  </dir>
</ul>
<ol start="2">
  <li>Please respect the deadline. As an author, you undoubtedly
appreciate the importance of minimizing delays. The paper selection
procedure for the Transactions involves a&nbsp; <span
 style="font-weight: bold;">recommendation</span> prepared by the
Associate Editor on the basis of paper reviews. The final <span
 style="font-weight: bold;">decision</span> on publication, sustaining
or modifying this recommendation, is taken by the Editor handling the
paper. If you do not have the time to personally review the paper,
please see if one of your qualified associates or senior graduate
students can review the paper, or else inform the Associate Editor
immediately and destroy your copy of the paper. In the latter case,
suggestions of names of alternate reviewers are appreciated. &nbsp;
&nbsp;</li>
</ol>
<ol start="3">
  <li>Please prepare your comments to the authors. Do not identify
yourself or your organization within the review text proper. The
following points are suggested for your comments: </li>
</ol>
<ul>
  <dir>
  <ul>
    <li>What is the contribution of the paper?</li>
    <li>Does the author explain the significance of this paper?</li>
    <li>Is the paper clearly written and well organized?</li>
    <li>Does the introduction state the purpose of the paper?</li>
    <li>Are the references relevant and complete? Supply missing
references. &nbsp; </li>
    <li>If the paper is not technically sound, why not? </li>
    <li>If the paper is too long, how can it be shortened? </li>
  </ul>
  </dir>
</ul>
<blockquote>Please supply any information that you think will be useful
to the author in revision, in enhancing the appeal of the paper, or in
convincing him/her of the mistakes. The reviewer's recommendation for
acceptance or rejection should not be included in the comments to the
author. It is very important that the reviewer include at least a few
sentences justifying his/her recommendation.&nbsp;</blockquote>
<ol start="5">
</ol>
<ol start="4">
  <li>In your critical comments to author, please be specific. If you
find that the results are already known, please give references to
earlier papers which contain these or similar results. If you say that
the reasoning is incorrect or vague, please indicate specifically where
and why. If you suggest that the paper be rewritten, give specific
suggestions as to which parts of the paper should be deleted, amplified
or modified, and please indicate how. <br>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>If you feel that additional material (equations, graphs, tables,
etc.) needs to be included in your review, please specify in your
comments that you have prepared a pdf file with such material. Send
then this file by email to the Associate Editor as an attachment. Since
this file will be forwarded to the author,&nbsp; please do not identify
yourself.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>It is sometimes the case that papers are passed on to senior
graduate students for review. Some very excellent reviews sometimes
result from this. It is important, though, that the quality and
professionalism of the review be maintained. If you pass the paper on
to a student to review, please check the review personally, and request
a copy of the review to be sent to you by providing your email address
and check "cc box" in the review form.</p>
  </li>
</ol>
<p style="text-align: center; color: rgb(204, 0, 0);"><big><font
 size="+1"><big><span style="font-weight: bold;">HOW TO DOWNLOAD A
PAPER FOR REVIEW</span></big></font> </big></p>
<div style="text-align: center; width: 756; height: 1480"><b>
</b>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span
 style="font-size: 12pt; font-weight: normal;">The paper is available
as a file&nbsp; in PDF or ps format in an outgoing directory of the FTP
site of the Transactions. In order to locate this file, please use the
information that the Associate Editor sent you by email.</span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span
 style="font-size: 12pt; font-weight: normal;">You
may use any ftp client program to download files (e.g. WS_FTP or
Internet
Explorer with Browsing Enhancements). Please note that file listing is
disabled on the Transactions FTP server so you will not see the files
in the outgoing
directory.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span
 style="font-size: 12pt; font-weight: normal;">WS_FTP
LE can be downloaded <a href="http://www.ftpplanet.com/download.htm">here</a>.
It is available for free to educational users, government employees
(U.S.
local, state, federal and military) or to non-business home users.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span
 style="font-size: 12pt; font-weight: normal;">Browsing
Enhancements is an optional component for Internet Explorer 5.x. It
allows
users to drag and drop files between remote ftp sites and the local
computer.
It is likely that this feature is already available on your computer.
If
it is not, please refer to the link below regarding how to install and
use FTP folders.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span
 style="font-size: 12pt; font-weight: normal;"><span style=""><a
 href="http://support.microsoft.com/default.aspx?scid=kb;EN-US;217888">http://support.microsoft.com/default.aspx?scid=kb;EN-US;217888</a></span><o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span
 style="font-size: 12pt; font-weight: normal;">Occasionally
people may have problems with FTP when their computers are behind some
firewalls and proxies. The workarounds include:<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p style="margin-left: 0.25in; text-indent: -0.25in; text-align: left;"><span
 style="font-size: 12pt; font-weight: normal;">1.<span
 style="font-family: &quot;Times New &quot;,Roman; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size-adjust: none;">&nbsp;</span></span><span
 style="font-size: 12pt; font-weight: normal;">Use
another ftp client program.</span></p>
<p style="margin-left: 0.25in; text-indent: -0.25in; text-align: left;"><span
 style="font-size: 12pt; font-weight: normal;">2.<span
 style="font-family: &quot;Times New &quot;,Roman; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size-adjust: none;">&nbsp;</span></span><span
 style="font-size: 12pt; font-weight: normal;">Use
a computer outside the current network.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span
 style="font-size: 12pt; font-weight: normal;">Please
report any technical problems to <b><a
 href="mailto:ieeetro@dis.uniroma1.it">ieeetro@dis.uniroma1.it</a></b>.</span></p>
